shared_text:
MFL MarMac Speech Team
March 30 at 9:41 AM ¬∑

TODAY, March 30 would have been the day for the All-State Individual Speech Festival at UNI. Our congratulations to our MFL MarMac speech participants who were chosen for these exceptional honors! We wish you could have had the experience of attending the festival, but we are very proud of all your accomplishments this year in Speech!

Congrats to Max Koeller for double recognition in both the Acting and Solo Musical Theater categories! Congrats to Dika Putri for Poetry, Jaxton Schroeder for Radio News Broadcasting, Nick Stavroplus for Spontaneous Speaking, and Jonah Wille for Storytelling!

MFL MarMac Speech Team
March 13 at 8:27 PM ¬∑

We are hosting our own State Individual Speech Contest tomorrow at MFL MarMac High School! Come watch the 20 MFL MarMac and 9 Lansing Kee students who advanced from the district contests and are vying for All-State honors.

[Note: the IHSSA approved having districts hire their own certified judges when the larger state speech contest had to be cancelled.]

So...come out and watch some awesome performances. You‚Äôll see a variety including solo musical theater, poetry/prose, acting, improvisation, after-dinner
speaking, radio news broadcasting, and more!

Performances begin at 8:30 am in the HS Library. The public is welcome!

Congratulations to the FIVE groups headed to STATE SPEECH on Saturday, Feb 8th!

Musical Theater: Max Koeller, Jaxton Schroeder, Abby Schellhorn, Riley Whitney, Rose Grau, and Nick Stavroplus.

Radio News: Dustin Berns, Haylee Guyer, Ty Eggers, Savannah Schaller, and Logan Brown.

The Bulldog dance team has been working hard to prepare for the ISDTA State Dance Competition... which is now just one month away! The team will be competing in 2 categories this year, Pom and Military. They perform at 9:30am and 5:35pm on Thursday, December 5th at the Wells Fargo Arena in Des Moines.

A special thanks goes to Coach Kelli Saxe for sharing her skills, teaching these students the importance of hard work, and building the confidence needed to compete and succeed! Go Bulldogs!

post_text: MFL MarMac High School is hosting an "impromptu" individual speech contest Monday, February 25th starting at 4:00 and ending at approx. 8:00. Saturday's weather made travel difficult to the regular district contest in Decorah... so 5 schools are participating in our contest with approximately 70 performances. We are asking parents of ALL the students who participated in group AND individual speech to please contact Angie Killian, Melissa Haberichter, or Diane Fisk to volunteer your time Monday evening. We will have limited concessions available. Parents, please send cookies, bars, and/or cupcakes to sell at the concession stand with your child on Monday. IF school is canceled on Monday, we will postpone the contest to Wednesday- same time and place. Speech contests are ALWAYS open to the public- come and enjoy a variety of performances! Your support is appreciated!!

post_text:
State Individual Speech Contest was quite amazing today! Thank you Scott Boylen and Diane Fisk for helping with transportation to Waldorf College. I am so proud of these kids... it has been a privilege to watch how they have grown through this experience. Students who received straight ones have a chance to be nominated by their judges to perform at the All State Festival at UNI March 27th. Students who were nominated by judges will be posted by Monday at 5:00 PM. So, now we wait.....LOL
Please congratulate ALL of these kids if you see them!! They are all talented and deserve recognition for their accomplishments!
Straight ones: Sierra Wiebensohn (Prose), Walter Stavroplus (Musical Theater), Max Koeller (Musical Theater), Micah Decker (Prose), Ayla Boylen (Poetry), Anjela Waterman (After Dinner Speaking AND Poetry), and Keagan Smerud (Poetry).
Overall ones: Hope McGlaughlin (Literary Program), Peyton Meisner (Radio News Announcing), Chelbe Feuerhelm (Storytelling), and Emma Ammons (Storytelling).
Straight two's: Walter Stavroplus (Improvisation).

On Saturday, February 25th our school is hosting the Iowa High School Speech Association (IHSSA) District Individual Speech Contest. There will be 20 schools with approximately 400 talented students traveling here to perform in their event. There is a total of 14 events showcased that day.
We are in need of many volunteers to make the contest run smoothly. Students can receive community service hours and adults are also needed. A free lunch is included for ALL who volunteer. Morning shifts are 7:15 to 11:30 and afternoon shifts are 11:30-4:00‚Ä¶.. or you CAN definitely work the entire day. Please contact me if you are interested in volunteering your time. My cell #563-581-7050 OR email me at killianam@mflmarmac.k12.ia.us. Thank you for supporting students involved in speech/debate and fine arts clubs!

Congratulations, Rose!

post_text: Congratulations to the students that performed at solo and ensemble contest today! We brought home 6 I's and 8 II's! Soloists that earned I's were A.J. VanWey and Micah Decker. Ensembles earning I's were "The Poet Sings", "Banks of Doon", "Tell My Father", and "This Train". Soloists that earned II's were Julie Lenth, Anjela Waterman, Corbin Gardner, Shae Routt, and Cheyenne Lachman. Ensembles receiving II's were "Land of Our Dreams", "Requiem", and the chamber choir. Great work today! A special thanks to Barb Ruff for accompanying and to all of the parents that came to listen to us today!

post_text: Individual State Speech Contest at Starmont was a success today! So proud of ALL of the students who participated. The kids have really increased their speaking and delivery skills as well as gaining more confidence. 8 out of our 16 events earned a one rating and these events have a shot at being nominated for ALL STATE. But more importantly, they are all learning real life public speaking skills to take with them for a lifetime. It was a privilege to watch all the performances today!!
